(Core Explanation) Tj
T*
(The central focus in Classification is taxonomic levels and reasons for grouping) Tj
T*
(organisms. A strong explanation should show the idea clearly, connect it to prior) Tj
T*
(knowledge, and then walk through the method students are expected to use whenever they) Tj
T*
(meet this topic in classwork or examination questions.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Understanding) Tj
T*
(A good classroom illustration for Classification is placing an organism into the correct) Tj
T*
(kingdom or class. When students can talk through that kind of example slowly and) Tj
T*
(correctly, they usually find it much easier to transfer the same reasoning to new) Tj
T*
(questions.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why Students Find It Difficult) Tj
T*
(One frequent problem in Classification is grouping by one obvious feature only. Students) Tj
T*
(also struggle when they try to memorize final answers without understanding the steps) Tj
T*
(that make the answer valid. Clear explanations, careful checking, and repeated guided) Tj
